      <description>Brodie S. Crump was the son of William Crump, the secretary and campaign
            manager of Mississippi politician, Leroy Percy. Leroy Percy received his law degree from
            the University of Virginia in 1881 and practiced law in his home town of Greenville,
            Mississippi. He served as a U.S. Senator from 1910 to 1912 and with the Federal Reserve
            Board branch in Saint Louis, Missouri, from 1914 until his death in
            1929.</description>
